  "In Leibniz notation, the chain rule is dy/dx = (dy/du)(du/dx). If y = f(u) and u = g(x), the derivative 'chains' through the intermediate variable u.": "在Leibniz 符号中,链规则是 dy/dx = (dy/du)(du/dx)。如果y = f(u) 和 u = g(x),则通过中间变量 u 的衍生“链 ” 。",
  "What does 'composition of functions' mean?": "“功能组合”意味着什么?",
