  "d/dx[n^x] = n^x * ln(n)": "ddx[nxx] = nx * in(n)",
  "The generalized power rule combines the power rule with the chain rule: d/dx[f(x)]^n = n[f(x)]^(n-1) * f'(x). It applies the power rule to the outer function and multiplies by the derivative of the inner function.": "通用权力规则将权力规则与链规则(d/dx[f(x)]n = n[f(x)](n-1)* f'(x))结合。该规则对外部功能适用权力规则,并通过内部函数的衍生物乘以权力规则。",
  "What does 'differentiating from the outside in' mean?": "\"与外界不同\"是什么意思?",
  "Evaluating the function at the boundary": "评估边界上的函数",
  "Differentiating the innermost function first": "首先区分内部函数",
  "Using the product rule before the chain rule": "在链规则之前使用产品规则",
  "Starting with the outermost function and working inward, multiplying by the derivative of each inner layer": "从最外层函数开始,向内工作,乘以每个内层的衍生物",
  "When differentiating a composite function, you work from outside in: first differentiate the outermost function (leaving inner functions intact), then multiply by the derivative of the next inner function, and continue inward.": "当区分复合函数时,您从外部工作到:首先区分外在函数(保持内部函数完整),然后乘以下一个内函数的衍生物,然后继续内向。",
